  "prompt": "What is \u2018double diameter\u2019 in a circle?",
  "response": "In a circle, the \"double diameter\" refers to the length of a line segment that passes through the center of the circle and has a length equal to twice the diameter. \n\nTo break this down:\n- Diameter is a line segment that passes through the center of the circle and has endpoints on the circle's circumference\n- Double diameter means a line segment that is twice the length of the diameter\n- This would extend beyond the circle's boundaries on both sides of the center point\n\nSo if a circle has a diameter of 5 units, the double diameter would be 10 units long.",
